HEADWORD: Uncharm
<hw>Un*charm"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>charm</ets>.]</ety> <def>To release from a charm,
fascination, or secret power; to disenchant.</def> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

